                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d192">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Brigadier
                        General <persName type="to">Henry A. Byroade</persName>, at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-13">13 February
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>186. Following, your 328<note n="37" xml:id="d192fn37">February 11, <ref
                            target="#pg_430">p. 430</ref>.</note> refers, information received from
                    General Chang Chih Chung through Colonel Pee regarding Canton area.
                    Generalissimo has issued order to General Chang Fa Kwei to allow Executive
                    Headquarters team to proceed to disputed area. This is <pb facs="0444" n="432"
                        xml:id="pg_432"/> interpreted by Pee as recognition by the National
                    Government to General Tseng Shang’s forces as Communists.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
